The spike ins used differed based on the days - on day 0 - e1 was used and on day 5 - e2. The dataframe lexogen contains the concentrations of the transcripts based on the number of the spike-in. If we divide each row of the counts matrix by the concentration of the spike-in in the sample based on the day - it should be roughly the same number in each column of the row.
